To make your application Tecla Accessible follow this procedure:

1. Include the package ca.idi.tecla.lib in your application.
2. Create an instance of the class InputAccess(say inputAccess) giving the activity whose options menu has to be made accessible as a parameter to the constructor.

A. To make the options menu accessible
1. Call the method inputAccess.onCreate() inside the activity's onCreate(Bundle) method.

Note:
1. The constructor is overloaded.

B. To make android.widget.Spinner accessible
1. Change the <Spinner></Spinner> tag in your xml layout file to the fully qualified custom Spinner class name. For eg., if the location of the custom Spinner class inside your src folder is /ca/idi/tecla/lib/Spinner.java than you should replace <Spinner> tags with <ca.idi.tecla.lib.Spinner>
2. Import the custom Spinner class instead of importing android.widget.Spinner in your code.

Demo programs:

Inaccessible version:
https://github.com/rishabhjain08/demo-inputaccesslib/tree/master/DemoInaccessibleOptionsMenu

Accessible version:
https://github.com/rishabhjain08/demo-inputaccesslib/tree/master/DemoAccessibleOptionsMenu